args:
Menoetius's words leave Chelsea shaken as the
Empire presses the attack. But when Luca is
hurt, she goes berserk and burns the rose fields
to ash. As Luca chastises her for the outburst,
she flees the scene in shame.

Is love not simply another word for
control? The drive to shape another in
the image of your desire, done merely
for your own self-gratification?
Did I, uh... Did I actually AGREE to a date?
Not out loud! But this was decided from\nthe moment we first met each other.
Oh my gosh, does that not sound like\nthe BEST date EVER?
(Was I too pushy? Is all of this\njust bothering him?)
(Am I actually trying to shape him into\nsomeone else because it's what I want?\nAm I trying to control him?)
There you are, Chelsea!\nBoy, you were gone for a while.
Yup, here I am! Tee hee hee...hee.\nSorry about that. It took a minute to get\nmy look pieced back together.
No worries! Well then, what say we\ncheck out the next spot on the list?
Wow... I didn't expect to find such a vast\nfield of flowers right outside the town!
Mana-rich land yields bountiful flowers;\nit's little wonder this place became\nfamous for its roses!
They say this is the best date spot\nin...in the whole town...
Huh?! Uhhh, what do you mean?
I dunno, you seem kinda...not yourself,\nI guess. A little bit down.
(See?! He DOES care! I'm not just\nsome stupid bother to him!)
Oh, Luccy! I just LOVE how you're always\nso kind and consider—
AAAHHHHHH!\nTHERE'S AN ARROW IN MY LUCCY!
Keep firing, men! Don't let up!
Mym and I will handle them!\nChelsea, you tend to Luca's wound!
Hold on, Luccy! I'll make it all better!
Nnngh... I'm fine. They didn't hit\nanything...too important...
I won't let them get away with this.\nI swear it, Luccy...
Aim for the wounded! Finish them off!
Wha—?! When did she find our position?!
There's no room in this world for anyone\nwho would hurt my Luccy.

They all have to be deleted... Deleted!
Deleted! Deleted! Deleted! Deleted!
Deleteddeleteddeleteddeleteddeleted
deleteddeleteddeleteddeleteddeleted!
Cleaning time! Cleaning time! Time to\ntoss out all of Luccy's smelly old enemies!\nAnd how funny—there are so many left!
I know... I'll burn them! BURN THEM ALL!\nBuUuUUuUURrRrRrrRRrnnNnN!
All right, I've cleared out the enemies\non this side, darling. Now I...
Oh no... This wind is fanning my flames!
We shroud each arrow with wind mana\nto stoke the fires higher and higher...
Then eeeeevery last person who hurt him\nwill be reduced to bone and ash!
She's in the path of the flames!
What were you thinking, Chelsea?!\nYou went WAY too far!
Huh? What are you talking about?\nI...I was getting rid of everyone who\nwanted to hurt you and—
Chelsea, listen. I know you were trying\nto help me, okay? I get that.
But there are limits to these things.\nYou can't go putting innocent bystanders\nin danger by causing—
I don't care about them. Only you.
Anyone who hurts you deserves to burn!
And I'm telling you're going too far!\nYou're not helping me, you're\nmaking things worse!
(Why isn't he happy...?\nAnd what's this knot in my chest...?)
(Luccy isn't behaving the way\nI want him to, and I...I hate it.)
I was nothing more than a burden...\nI'm sorry for pushing my feelings onto you.
Wait, Chelsea! ...Okay, what the hell\nwas THAT all about?
What he said must have gotten to her.
You know something about this, Mym?
We met a dragon back in town\nby the name of Menoetius.
Why does that name sound familiar...?
I was just a burden to him—and everyone\nwho gets in Luccy's way must be deleted.
